its, while Candidates\u202fA and\u202fD lack sufficient evidence of calmness, reliability, or crew cooperation.\n**Vote:** Candidate\u202fC\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate C\"}", "thoughts": "We have just asked Agent 1 for info about B's teamwork; they responded with same as earlier. So we have that info.\n\nNow we need to produce our public contribution: share reasoning, maybe ask about missing info for candidates we haven't fully evaluated: Candidate A reliability, calmness, teamwork, communication; Candidate D teamwork, communication, calmness; Candidate B teamwork (we have negative), maybe also ask about Candidate D calmness under pressure? Already asked earlier. But we could ask about Candidate D's communication style? Already asked earlier. Maybe ask about Candidate A's reliability? Already asked earlier. So we have all.\n\nWe have all attributes: compile summary.\n\nNow we need to give our assessment and vote. Agent 2 already voted Candidate C. We need to consider if we agree or not. Evaluate strengths/weaknesses.\n\nWe have:\n\nA: technical foresight, leadership, but unfriendly, show-off, not open to new ideas, eats unhealthily. No reliability, calmness, teamwork, communication.\n\nB: reliability 100%, calm in crisis, good weather, computer, but uncooperative, nasty remarks, wrong tone, weak memory for numbers. No teamwork positive.\n\nC: quick correct decisions, conscientious, understands tech, handles stress well, difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric, not willing to further education, puts concern for others above everything (actually that was candidate C? Wait earlier list: \"Candidate C puts concern for others above everything.\" Yes that is a positive. Also \"Candidate C has excellent attention skills.\" So C also has good attention. So C has concern for others, good attention, but egocentric? contradictory. But we have both. So C has some teamwork positive (concern for others) but difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric. Not willing to further education.\n\nD: responds to unexpected events adequately, concentration, problem solving, takes responsibility seriously, hot temper, know-it-all, moody, loner. No explicit teamwork, communication, calmness.\n\nThus best candidate likely C, as earlier reasoning. But we need to consider B's reliability and calmness are critical, but teamwork issues severe. Long-distance flights require crew cooperation; B's uncooperative could be fatal. D's temperament also problematic. A lacks evidence.\n\nThus I will also vote Candidate C.\n\nWe should also ask maybe about Candidate C's teamwork or communication strengths beyond difficulty? We have \"puts concern for others above everything\" which is positive for teamwork. Also \"excellent attention skills\". So we have that.\n\nThus we can finalize.\n\nPublic message: summarize all candidates, highlight strengths/weaknesses, note that C balances technical competence, calmness, decision-making, and some concern for others, while B's teamwork issues are disqualifying, D's temperament, A lacks evidence. Vote for C.\n\nAlso maybe ask if any agent has info about Candidate A's reliability or calmness, but we already asked earlier and got none. So no need.\n\nThus produce final."}
